author: tomj
msg: Fix a problem in the type mapping registry: We were unconditionally setting
the type mapping for the SOAP encoding.  This would overwrite any type
mappings for that encoding defined in the WSDD files, which wasn't very nice
Check for the existance of a type mapping, and if we find one, make sure
its default TM points to the one we want - specifically the JAXRPC 1.1 default

author: dicka
msg: Add in support of remaining XSD datatypes for deserialization within engine.
Included with this piece of work, I have modified the engine such that deserialization of each data element is carried out at the latest oppurtunity.
In addition I have tidied up redundant code and a number of macros in this area.
All changes have been fully tested on AIX, Linux and Windows.
